-- Croatia to Invest 1 Billion Kuna in Public Buildings, HINA Says
-- B y   J a s m i n a   K u z m a n o v i c
-- 2012-03-13T12:46:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-13/croatia-to-invest-1-billion-kuna-in-public-buildings-hina-says.html
Croatia will invest 1 billion kuna
($173 million) to renovate public buildings over the next few
years to stimulate  construction industry  and save energy costs,
national  news agency   HINA  reported, citing Ivan Vrdoljak, the
minister of  construction and physical planning .  The government is in talks with the  European Bank for
Reconstruction and Development  and  HBOR , the national
reconstruction bank, to finance the project, according to HINA.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jasmina Kuzmanovic in Zagreb at 
 jkuzmanovic@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  